==English==

===Etymology===
Originated in North America.  An Anglo-America colonists' slang term describing young Indian men, who in warm weather often hunted and fought without clothing.

===Alternative forms===
*[[buck-naked]]

===Adjective===
'''[[buck]] [[naked]]'''

# Completely naked
# Naked but for a waist band with knife sheath, arm bands, footwear, weapons in hand, etc.  

====Synonyms====
*[[butt naked]]